title: Teenager Accused Of Stabbing Man At Sioux Falls Apartment
text:
Teenager Accused Of Stabbing Man At Sioux Falls Apartment October 20, 2015, 11:20 AM by Anna Peters SIOUX FALLS, SD - 
A Sisseton teenager is behind bars, accused of stabbing a man with a scissors and hitting him over the head with a toilet seat. 
Sioux Falls Police were called to an eastside apartment late Monday morning. They found the victim in a bathroom, attempting to clean himself up. He'd been stabbed in his neck, shoulder, chest and wrist and couldn't remember what happened. Police later caught up with 18-year old Bruce Godfrey, Jr. He's charged with aggravated assault and underage consumption. 
Authorities believe both men had been drinking. Â© 2015 KELOLAND TV. All Rights Reserved.
